+# HMAC Auth API
+
+Small Express API that issues and validates HMAC-signed bearer tokens for a
+mock workspace service.
+
+## Local development
+
+1. Install dependencies with `npm ci`.
+2. Set `HMAC_SECRET` before starting the app or running tests.
+3. Optionally set `PORT`; the app defaults to `3000`.
+
+Common commands:
+
+- `npm run dev` to start the API locally
+- `npm test` to run the test suite
+- `npm run build` to compile TypeScript
+
+## Getting a token
+
+Request a token from `POST /auth/token` with JSON like:
+
+```json
+{
+  "email": "alice@example.com",
+  "password": "correct-horse-battery-staple"
+}
+```
+
+The response returns a bearer token that can be used with the `/users` and
+`/workspaces` routes.
+
+## Health check
+
+`GET /health` returns the current service status and runtime environment.
